  "A startup has two financing options: (A) a $100,000 bank loan at 7% for 10 years (monthly payment ~$1,161), or (B) giving up 15% equity to an angel investor (business valued at $100,000). If the business grows to $1,000,000 in 10 years, which option costs more?": "",
